                            <comment id="67175" author="rstoya05-aop" created="Wed, 8 Jun 2011 05:05:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Although 3.1 already has a &quot;produces&quot; condition in @RequestMapping, currently it works of the &apos;Accept&apos; header only. A more comprehensive update in this area is planned for 3.2 (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-8410&quot; title=&quot;Content negotiation improvements&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-8410&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-8410&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="80917" author="rstoya05-aop" created="Fri, 22 Jun 2012 09:32:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is now resolved. To configure detecting requested media types through URL path extensions, declare a ContentNegotiationManager bean and use it in the RequestMappingHandlerMapping (for matches via the produces condition), the RequestMappingHandlerAdapter and the ExceptionHandlerExceptionResolver (for writing to the response body).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
